  "local_port": 53198,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I have a very old account in central bank in which no mobile number is registered. How to register my mobile number now?",
  "response": "To register or update your mobile number in your central bank account, follow these general steps. Since procedures may vary slightly depending on the specific central bank or its online system, it's advisable to check the bank's official website or contact their customer service for precise instructions.\n\nHere\u2019s a general guide:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Visit the Bank\u2019s Website**\n   - Go to the official website of your central bank.\n   - Look for a section related to \"Online Banking,\" \"Account Services,\" or \"Customer Support.\"\n\n---\n\n### **2. Log in to Your Account**\n   - Use your existing credentials to log in to your online banking account.\n   - If you don\u2019t have online banking access, proceed to step 3.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Updating Mobile Number Online**\n   - If available, look for an option like \"Profile Update,\" \"Personal Details,\" or \"Contact Information.\"\n   - Enter your new mobile number and verify it using an OTP (One-Time Password) sent to your email or another registered contact method.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Visit a Branch (If Online Option Is Not Available)**\n   - If you cannot update your mobile number online, visit the nearest central bank branch.\n   - Carry valid identification (e.g., passport, national ID, or driver\u2019s license) and your account details.\n   - Fill out the required form to update your mobile number. Some banks may require a physical signature.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Use Customer Service**\n   - If visiting a branch is inconvenient, call the bank\u2019s customer service helpline.\n   - Provide your account details and request them to update your mobile number.\n   - They may guide you through an online process or arrange a call-back verification.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Verify the Update**\n   - Once your mobile number is updated, ensure it\u2019s verified by receiving a confirmation SMS or email from the bank.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n   - Keep your account details and ID proof ready for faster processing.\n   - If your account is dormant or inactive, the bank may require you to reactivate it before updating your details.\n   - If you face any issues, escalate the matter to the bank\u2019s higher authorities or grievance redressal cell.\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
